  <h1>Plate</h1>
  <h3>Source</h3>
  <text>
    <style color="0xaaaaaa" italic="true">Note: this page is ported from MCMOD's GTCEu wiki. <br></br> Author: <style color="0xa4e7ff" hover-info="url" underlined="true" url-link="https://center.mcmod.cn/119280/">Oganesson897</style> <br></br>, <style color="0xa4e7ff" hover-info="url" underlined="true" url-link="https://github.com/blackdragon2447">BlackDragon2447</style> <br></br></style>
  </text>
  <text>Plates are your most basic (non ingot) material item, being used in a wide range of applications, among which is the creation of machine casings and hulls, or processing into foil.</text>
  <h3>Crafting</h3>
  <text>The creation of plates is initially done manually, using a hammer for a two to one ratio (ingots to plates), during the steam age the <style color="0xafff00" hover-info="click link" link="gtceu:machines/forge_hammer" underlined="true">Forge Hammer</style> can (and should) be used to create plates at a three to two ratio, during the lv (and later) age a <style color="0xafff00" hover-info="click link" link="gtceu:machines/bender" underlined="true">Bender</style> can be created to make plates at a one to one ratio. Plates can also be made from blocks in a <style color="0xafff00" hover-info="click link" link="gtceu:machines/cutter" underlined="true">Cutter</style> or from ingots in an <style color="0xafff00" hover-info="click link" link="gtceu:machines/extruder" underlined="true">Extruder</style>.</text>
